{
    "id": "electronics/basic-circuit",
    "title": "Build a basic LED circuit",
    "description": "Learn the basics of circuits by wiring an LED with a current-limiting resistor on a breadboard.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/basic_circuit.svg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Hey there! I'm Orion. Ready to see how simple electronics can be? We'll wire a 5 mm LED with a 220 Ω resistor on a breadboard and keep things safe.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "Sure, what do I need?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials",
            "text": "Gather a breadboard, two jumper wires, a 5 mm LED, a 220 Ω resistor and a 5 V power supply (battery pack or USB adapter). Keep the supply unplugged while wiring; the resistor protects the LED from too much current. Ready to assemble?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "assemble",
                    "text": "Yep, let's assemble it.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 2
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "48cf736e-184c-4bd1-b9b0-15b7e9721646",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "037e6065-68a7-4ad1-9b0b-7778ecfe0662",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "828d6c3b-66a5-4064-b221-97630274502b",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "assemble",
            "text": "Insert the LED into the breadboard with the long leg (anode) on the positive rail. Place the 220 Ω resistor from the anode's row to a new row, then use jumper wires to link the resistor to +5 V and the LED's short leg (cathode) to ground. Confirm the resistor is in series and polarity is correct before applying power. When it all looks secure, connect the 5 V power supply and the LED should glow.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "It works!"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Great job! You've built your first circuit and lit up an LED. Always disconnect power before changing any connections.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Thanks, Orion!"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
